***Setting Environmental variable to store the GPT-3 API key***

-set up and access environment variables on a Windows system:

-Set an Environment Variable for the API Key:

    Open the Start menu and search for "Environment Variables" or "Edit the system environment variables."

    Click the "Environment Variables" button.

    In the "System variables" section, click "New" to create a new environment variable.

    Set the variable name, OPENAI_API_KEY, and provide the corresponding API key as the variable value.

    Click "OK" to save the environment variable.

    To verify the setup, reopen the command prompt and type the command below. It should display your API key: echo %OPENAI_API_KEY%
